  "prompt": "What are some ways to take screenshots my desktop?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to take screenshots on different devices:\n\nWindows:\n1. PrtScn (Print Screen) key - Copies entire screen to clipboard\n2. Alt + PrtScn - Captures active window\n3. Windows + PrtScn - Saves screenshot automatically\n4. Snipping Tool - Built-in Windows screenshot utility\n5. Snip & Sketch - Newer Windows screenshot app\n6. Third-party apps like Greenshot or ShareX\n\nMac:\n1. Command + Shift + 3 - Entire screen\n2. Command + Shift + 4 - Select specific area\n3. Command + Shift + 4, then Spacebar - Capture specific window\n4. Screenshot app\n5. Preview app\n\nChrome OS:\n1. Ctrl + Show Windows key (rectangle icon)\n2. Ctrl + Shift + Show Windows key\n3. Alt + Show Windows key\n\nMobile Devices:\n1. Power + Volume Down (Android)\n2. Power + Home button (older iOS)\n3. Power + Volume Up (newer iOS)\n4. Built-in screenshot tools in device settings\n\nOnline/Browser Screenshots:\n1. Browser extensions\n2. Online screenshot tools\n3. Web-based screenshot services\n\nEach method has specific advantages depending on your needs and device.",
